    <h3>Community Information</h3>
    <p>Voted as the "36th Best Place to Live In the Nation", Gilbert, Arizona is located in
southwestern America. With an average of 310 sunny days per year, the climate is perfect
for outdoor fun, no matter the month. Known for being a bicycle and tree friendly city,
Gilbert is not only environmentally conscious, but a safe place to live. Tourists travel to
visit the Gilbert Riparian Preserve, the Gilbert Observatory, and all the Big League Dreams,
which composes eight ball fields for the public to enjoy. Golf is also a favorite way to
past the time at the Trilogy Golf Club, right next to the Santan Mountains. With a vibrant
downtown district full of theater, dining and shopping in open-air areas, there is something
for everyone in Gilbert!</p>
